description: When using the US International Keyboard, single quotes (') and double quotes (") are "dead keys". This is fine if you want to use Umlauts (äöüÄÖÜ). If you're a software developer however that in addition to Umlauts also that relies on those qoutes to work as non-dead (i.e. regular) keys, this behavior is annoying. The Keyboard Manager in Microsoft PowerToys has you covered. Use the US International Layout as the default keyboard layout and add this settings below to PowerToys.
